
[1]incest

   IN'CEST, n. [L. incestum; in and castus, chaste.]

   The crime of cohabitation or sexual commerce between persons related
   within the degrees wherein marriage is prohibited by the law of a
   country.

   Spiritual incest, is a like crime committed between persons who have a
   spiritual alliance by means of baptism or confirmation. It is also
   understood of a vicar or other beneficiary, who holds two benefices,
   the one depending on the collation of the other.
